BA_ "Description" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_Crc1Val "The data area for CRC calculation is based on the data length (DLC) of the message DB.
The CRC shall be calculated over the entire data block (excluding the CRC bytes) including the user data, alive counter and Data ID
 
- CRC Polynomial (0x1021) , Initial Value : 0xFFFF, XOR value : 0x0000, Data ID : Message ID + 0xF800 
- The initial value is for CRC calculation and the message should be sent with the calculated result value. 
- The mathematical expression to 16 bit CRC polynomial is given here. G(x) = x16 + x12 + x5 + 1";
BA_ "GenSigStartValue" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_Crc1Val 65535;
BA_ "UserSigValidity" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_Crc1Val 3;
BA_ "NetworkRequestHoldingTime" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_Crc1Val 0;
BA_ "RoutingFactor" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_Crc1Val 1;
BA_ "Version" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_Crc1Val "18.11.08";
BA_ "Description" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_AlvCnt1Val "For the first transmission request for a data element the counter shall be initialized with 0 and shall be incremented by 1 for every subsequent send request. 
When the counter reaches the maximum value(0xFF), then it shall restart with 0 for the next send request";
BA_ "GenSigStartValue" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_AlvCnt1Val 0;
BA_ "UserSigValidity" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_AlvCnt1Val 3;
BA_ "NetworkRequestHoldingTime" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_AlvCnt1Val 0;
BA_ "RoutingFactor" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_AlvCnt1Val 1;
BA_ "Version" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_AlvCnt1Val "18.11.08";
BA_ "Description" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_SysWrngLmpDis "This signal means information regarding ACU diagnostic information result & discrimination.

1) Default value : 0x1
2) Default value Transmit condition
    - When the input condition is not determined.
    - When the input condition is not supported.";
BA_ "GenSigStartValue" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_SysWrngLmpDis 1;
BA_ "UserSigValidity" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_SysWrngLmpDis 3;
BA_ "NetworkRequestHoldingTime" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_SysWrngLmpDis 0;
BA_ "RoutingFactor" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_SysWrngLmpDis 1;
BA_ "Version" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_SysWrngLmpDis "18.11.05";
BA_ "Description" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_TlltlLmpDis "This signal means information regarding Occupant status.
0) 00Xb : X position means PAB OFF Lamp indication. When this bit set as 1 PAB OFF lamp turns ON. 
    0Y0b : Y position means PAB ON Lamp indication. When this bit set as 1 PAB ON lamp turns ON.

1) Default value : 0x2 (PAB ON Lamp on, PAB OFF Lamp off,)
2) Default value Transmit condition
    - When the input condition is not determined.
    - When the input condition is not supported.";
BA_ "GenSigStartValue" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_TlltlLmpDis 3;
BA_ "UserSigValidity" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_TlltlLmpDis 3;
BA_ "NetworkRequestHoldingTime" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_TlltlLmpDis 0;
BA_ "RoutingFactor" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_TlltlLmpDis 1;
BA_ "Version" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_TlltlLmpDis "20.03.02";
BA_ "Description" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_OdsIDReq "It s a Request to send ODS Identifier. If the Bit is equal to `0` the ODS-B module will transmit the ODS identifier message. ACU sets ˇ°ODS ID Receivedˇ± to ˇ®1ˇŻ after getting the valid ODS ID two times.

1) Default value : 0x0
2) Default value Transmit condition
    - When the input condition is not determined.
    - When the input condition is not supported.";
BA_ "GenSigStartValue" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_OdsIDReq 0;
BA_ "UserSigValidity" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_OdsIDReq 3;
BA_ "NetworkRequestHoldingTime" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_OdsIDReq 0;
BA_ "RoutingFactor" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_OdsIDReq 1;
BA_ "Version" SG_ 2281835009 ACU_OdsIDReq "17.12.00";
BA_ "Description" SG_ 2281835009 SeatBelt_PassBcklFltSta "Information of Passenger Seat Belt Buckle switch Fault condition.

1) Default value : 0x0
2) Default value Transmit condition
    - When the input condition is not supported.
ˇŘThis signal is valid (updated) only that buckle is connected to ACU directly, 
otherwise transmitted as default value.";
BA_ "GenSigStartValue" SG_ 2281835009 SeatBelt_PassBcklFltSta 0;
BA_ "UserSigValidity" SG_ 2281835009 SeatBelt_PassBcklFltSta 3;
BA_ "NetworkRequestHoldingTime" SG_ 2281835009 SeatBelt_PassBcklFltSta 0;
