BA_ "Description" SG_ 2256644609 CLU_DisSpdDcmlVal "The signal 'CF_Clu_VanzDecimal' means the extra value of the signal 'CF_Clu_Vanz' (vehicle speed which is indicated in the speedometer)
Also, This signal should be sent in km/h or MPH according to the 'CF_Clu_SPEED_UNIT' signal.
CF_Clu_SPEED_UNIT = 0 : [km/h]
CF_Clu_SPEED_UNIT = 1 : [MPH]

Example)   CF_Clu_Vanz = 13,  CF_Clu_VanzDecimal  = 3
Displayed vehicle speed  = (CF_Clu_Vanz / 2) + (CF_Clu_VanzDecimal / 8)
= ( 13 / 2 ) + ( 3 / 8 ) = 6.875 [Km/h or MPH]";
BA_ "GenSigStartValue" SG_ 2256644609 CLU_DisSpdDcmlVal 0;
BA_ "UserSigValidity" SG_ 2256644609 CLU_DisSpdDcmlVal 3;
