BA_ "Description" SG_ 2193667330 ENG_IsgSta "1. ISG Status expressing CAN message divided by CF_EMS_IsgStat and CF_EMS_IsgStat2 
2. In EMS , CF_EMS_IsgStat and CF_EMS_IsgStat2 do not duplicate the output condition
(EX: If CF_EMS_IsgStat is 01h~07h, CF_EMS_IsgStat2 is 00h)

0x0:ISG is not operating Normal engine operating without ISG/0x1:Idle stop is activated Idle is stopped by ECU during driving/0x2:Automatically started by ECU Engine is automatically started by ECU regardless driverˇŻs volition during idle stop because the condition that ISG function to be prohibited is satisfied, for example SOC is too low./0x3:ISG is prohibited Driver prohibits to activate ISG in order to avoid start lag when he met traffic jam for example./0x4:Fault is existing in ISG There is fault, which is related with ISG. So, idle stop is prohibited and engine started automatically if it is idle stop condition. But for the vehicles that use CF_EMS_ISGStat2, the condition for not-activated battery sensor can be ignored./0x5:Idle stop is inhibited by system automatically for safety and  convenient condition related with battery SOC, brake vacuum pressure etc. ISG function check for EOL./0x6:Auto start is deactivated system automatically to keep safety, Such as door open, hood open and seat belt unlock./0x7:If driver shift gear N to D range without braking to make auto starting. (Economy ISG Only)";
BA_ "GenSigStartValue" SG_ 2193667330 ENG_IsgSta 0;
BA_ "UserSigValidity" SG_ 2193667330 ENG_IsgSta 3;
