BA_ "Description" SG_ 2193667331 ENG_SldActnSta "This signal indicates that if positive action of a driver at speed limiter function is active or not. If the positive action is activated then CF_Ems_SldPosAct = 1, which let the current vehicle speed to exceed the limit speed set from a driver.
If kick-down switch isnˇŻt connected to engine ECU directly, ECU can recognize the positive action of a driver from accel pedal position indirectly.
When current vehicle speed exceeds the limit speed, vehicle reaction should be distinguished (e.g. lamp reaction or audio warning signal reaction) depending on the status of ˇ°CF_Ems_SldPosActˇ±";
