BA_ "Description" SG_ 2214658049 ENG_MafCrctVal "The altitude correction factor MAF_FAC_ALTI_MMV is calculated from division of MAF by MAF_SUB_DIAG (=limp home-value for MAF) or from AMP_AD by 1013 mbar in order to take into account different atmospheric pressures at different altitudes.

The Initial-value of 1.0 indicates sea-level, whereas lower values indicate altitude. MAF_FAC_ALTI_MMV is limited to C_MAF_FAC_ALTI_MMV_MIN (=0.6) and C_MAF_FAC_ALTI_MMV_MAX (=1.1) by calibration.";
