BA_ "VFrameFormat" BO_ 2214658051 1;
BA_ "Description" SG_ 2214658051 ENG_MinIndTqVal "The signal TQI_MIN is the minimum engine torque (minimum air charging rate) which can be fired without misfire including compensation factors such as atmospheric pressure and temperature.
It is not enough to keep the engine running without external power such as inertia.
Firing is impossible below TQI_MIN even if engine is turning by inertia. The friction torque is
always greater than TQI_MIN which is almost constant value across engine RPM.
This signal is used to determine when activation of automatic braking is required to achieve a certain deceleration or if the engine deceleration is sufficient under current conditions.

Under normal driving conditions the physical value of this signal is negative:
TQ_MIN[Nm] = TQI_MIN[Nm] - TQFR[Nm]

If MSB is 1, this signal is - value.
else, this signal is +value.
0~10bit is used for absolute value.";
BA_ "GenSigStartValue" SG_ 2214658051 ENG_MinIndTqVal 0;
BA_ "UserSigValidity" SG_ 2214658051 ENG_MinIndTqVal 3;
BA_REL_ "GenSigTimeoutTime" BU_SG_REL_ AMP SG_ 2214658051 ENG_MinIndTqVal 500;
BA_ "NetworkRequestHoldingTime" SG_ 2214658051 ENG_MinIndTqVal 0;
BA_ "RoutingFactor" SG_ 2214658051 ENG_MinIndTqVal 5;
BA_ "Version" SG_ 2214658051 ENG_MinIndTqVal "18.01.01";
BA_ "Description" SG_ 2214658051 ENG_TrgtTqVal "The signal TQI_TARGET is determined by an engine torque map with input which consists of  acceleration pedal value, MAF sensor, current RPM and etc. This signal reflects driverˇŻs demand directly. 
But it does not depend on torque interventions realised due to reduction of airflow into the engine cylinders and due to ignition angle adjustment or injection/cylinder shut off.

In case of failures of the load signal (either MAF error or other errors depending on the system congiguration), a backup value is generated from specific index tables. The backup value mode is identified by the signal F_SUB_TQI. 

There is a specific phase relationship between the signals TQI_TARGET and F_SUB_TQI.

If MSB is 1, this signal is - value.
else, this signal is +value.
0~10bit is used for absolute value.";
BA_ "GenSigStartValue" SG_ 2214658051 ENG_TrgtTqVal 0;
BA_ "UserSigValidity" SG_ 2214658051 ENG_TrgtTqVal 3;
BA_ "NetworkRequestHoldingTime" SG_ 2214658051 ENG_TrgtTqVal 0;
BA_ "RoutingFactor" SG_ 2214658051 ENG_TrgtTqVal 5;
BA_ "Version" SG_ 2214658051 ENG_TrgtTqVal "18.01.01";
BA_ "Description" SG_ 2214658051 ENG_MaxIndTqVal "The signal TQI_MAX is the current maximum indicated engine torque. This signal reflects the maximum engine torque under current conditions (engine speed, etcˇ¦).

Note : TQI_MAX must be transmitted actual engine torque including COT, thermal/spark efficiency etc..
 This means that the TQI_ACOR can reach to the TQI_MAX.
 If not possible, thTQI_MAX should be ˇ° FFHˇ± (99.6%) to reduce TCS/ESC variant.

TQ_MAX[Nm] = TQI_MAX[Nm] - TQFR[Nm]

If MSB is 1, this signal is - value.
else, this signal is +value.
0~10bit is used for absolute value.";
BA_ "GenSigStartValue" SG_ 2214658051 ENG_MaxIndTqVal 0;
BA_ "UserSigValidity" SG_ 2214658051 ENG_MaxIndTqVal 3;
BA_REL_ "GenSigTimeoutTime" BU_SG_REL_ AMP SG_ 2214658051 ENG_MaxIndTqVal 500;
BA_ "NetworkRequestHoldingTime" SG_ 2214658051 ENG_MaxIndTqVal 0;
BA_ "RoutingFactor" SG_ 2214658051 ENG_MaxIndTqVal 5;
BA_ "Version" SG_ 2214658051 ENG_MaxIndTqVal "18.01.01";
