BA_ "Description" SG_ 2307022849 ENG_AtmsphPrsrVal "The value AMP_CAN specifies the atmospheric pressure in the unit [mmHg]. It is calculated from the altitude correction factor MAF_FAC_ALTI_MMV. (Modeling Value)
However, when AMP sensor is equipped, the value AMP_CAN is calculated from the sensor output value.

The Hex-Limits for AMP_CAN are 0 ... 1FH (0 ... 31 dec; 5 Bit) and the physical output is limited to 458.98 ... 792.78 mmHg.

Calculation of AMP_CAN: 
AMP_CAN [hex] = ( MAF_FAC_ALTI_MMV [dec] - 77 [dec] ) * 0.5535714";
BA_ "GenSigStartValue" SG_ 2307022849 ENG_AtmsphPrsrVal 28;
BA_ "UserSigValidity" SG_ 2307022849 ENG_AtmsphPrsrVal 3;
BA_ "NetworkRequestHoldingTime" SG_ 2307022849 ENG_AtmsphPrsrVal 0;
