BA_ "Description" SG_ 1067 SCM_SWVerMajor1 "Indicate the SCM software version as follows:
- The software version is displayed in three digits.
- The Major and Minor digits are separated by '.'
- Signal values are transmitted to ASCII codes.

ˇŘ Example
SCM_SWVerMajor1 : 0x41 (HEX) -> ASCII CODE : 'A' 
SCM_SWVerMinor1 : 0x30 (HEX) -> ASCII CODE : '0'
SCM_SWVerMinor2 : 0x33 (HEX) -> ASCII CODE : '3'
=> SCM S/W Ver is displayed 'A.03'";
